The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during an event at the White House to celebrate African American History Month. The President expressed gratitude for the contributions of African Americans to American life and recognized the sacrifices made by African American heroes in the pursuit of freedom and civil rights. He also highlighted the achievements of his administration, such as low African American unemployment rates, criminal justice reform, and the creation of new jobs. The President emphasized his commitment to expanding opportunities for Americans of all races and backgrounds. Several notable guests, including Surgeon General Jerome Adams and individuals who have benefited from criminal justice reform, were also acknowledged during the event.